# Build artifacts
/target/
/**/target/
/build/
/artifacts/
/target-os2vm/

# Rust toolchains & caches (anywhere)
**/.rustup/
**/.cargo/

# Images/logs
*.img
*.iso
*.nxb
*.log
build/*.log

# Auto-generated runtime artefacts.
#
# Special case: `uart.log` is BOTH tracked (HEAD carries a snapshot) and
# listed here. Rationale:
#   * `make test`/`make run`/`scripts/qemu-test.sh` rewrite the working-tree
#     copy on every QEMU run, so without the ignore line every run would
#     show as `M uart.log` and pollute `git add .` flows.
#   * The HEAD copy is task-closure evidence: the canonical marker ladder
#     captured at the moment the responsible task was closed.
#
# Policy: do NOT stage `uart.log` on every run. Only refresh the tracked
# snapshot when closing a task that legitimately changes the marker ladder
# or boot output. Use `git add -f uart.log` deliberately in that closure
# commit. The mtime-only "M" noise during day-to-day work is intentional
# and must be ignored.
uart.log
uart_ecall_chars.log
neuron-boot.map
uart_syspipe*.txt
uart_syspipe.txt

# TASK-0023B Phase 5 — sealed evidence bundles (P5-02 onward).
# `target/evidence/<utc>-<profile>-<git-sha>.tar.gz` is a per-run
# audit artifact; never staged, never committed.
target/evidence/

# TASK-0023B Phase 5 — Ed25519 private-key material (P5-04). The CI
# private key is stored as a CI secret (env var
# NEXUS_EVIDENCE_CI_PRIVATE_KEY_BASE64) and the bringup private key
# lives at ~/.config/nexus/bringup-key/private.ed25519. Belt-and-
# braces: refuse to track any *.private.ed25519 / *.priv.* file
# anywhere in the tree.
keys/*.private.ed25519
keys/*.priv.ed25519
**/private.ed25519
**/*.priv.ed25519

# 2-VM harness artifacts (TASK-0005 / RFC-0010)
uart-*.txt
host-*.txt
*.pcap

# Temporary test logs
test-uart.txt
tmp-uart.txt
tmp*.txt

# Cursor IDE logs
.cursor-*.log

# Temporary debug/extract files
tmp*.rs

# TASK-0023B Phase 6 — replay/bisect scratch (legacy; current tooling
# uses target/replay-worktree and target/replay-cache which are already
# covered by /target/). Keep .tmp/ ignored to absorb any leftover
# scratch from earlier replay runs.
.tmp/
